This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Cybersecurity (cs.CY) as it deals with the security and stability of cryptocurrency markets. It could also belong to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) as it studies the influence of peer behavior on market dynamics. Additionally, it could be classified under the sub-category of Social and Economic Systems (cs.SOC) as it examines the impact of design choices on market behavior. The paper also involves Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) as it discusses the potential social and economic impact of HCI in the design of digital institutions. Finally, it could be classified under the sub-category of Game Theory (cs.GT) as it studies the behavior of traders in a market setting.
